### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

_No response_

### Description

`Testbed` based tests are quite verbose in a _zoneless_ setup.
**Every** test needs to declare `provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection()` as a provider:

```ts
 beforeEach(() => {
    TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      providers: [
        provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection(),
      ],
      // ...
    });
  });

// tests here...
```

When  `provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection()` is omitted in `Testbed`:
```sh
Error: NG0908: In this configuration Angular requires Zone.js
        error properties: Object({ code: 908 })
```

### Proposed solution

Idea 1

 When zone.js is missing in the  `polyfills` of `@angular-devkit/build-angular:karma` _angular_  should include `provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection`implicitly. This has the drawback that its tied to `@angular-devkit/build-angular:karma`, so probably not a good idea, because there are many different other popular test setups for angular.

```json5
// angular.json
 "test": {
    "builder": "@angular-devkit/build-angular:karma",
    "options": {
      "tsConfig": "tsconfig.spec.json",
      "karmaConfig": "karma.config.cjs"
      "polyfills": ["some-polyfills"] // no zone.js => zoneless Testbed setup
    }
  }
```

Idea 2

add a flag to `TestBed.initTestEnvironment()`

```ts
TestBed.initTestEnvironment(
  BrowserDynamicTestingModule,
  platformBrowserDynamicTesting(),
  {
    ngZone: false // and then in some majors default it to true

    errorOnUnknownElements: true,
    errorOnUnknownProperties: true,
  },
);
```

Idea 3

Allow users to explicitly declare `provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection()` in `TestBed.initTestEnvironment()`

```ts
TestBed.initTestEnvironment(
  BrowserDynamicTestingModule,
  // ts error: Type 'EnvironmentProviders' is not assignable to type 'StaticProvider'.
  platformBrowserDynamicTesting([provideExperimentalZonelessChangeDetection()]),
  {
    errorOnUnknownElements: true,
    errorOnUnknownProperties: true,
  },
);
```

### Alternatives considered

see ideas

