### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

router

### Description

Add support for named routes in Angular Router, similar to Vue Router's implementation, to improve route management and navigation.

Currently, Angular Router requires using URLs or paths for navigation. Named routes would provide:

- More maintainable route definitions
- Type-safe navigation
- Easier refactoring when URLs change
- Better developer experience

### Proposed solution

## Proposed Solution

### Route Definition
```typescript
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'products',
    name: 'products.list',  // New property
    component: ProductListComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'products/:id',
    name: 'products.detail',
    component: ProductDetailComponent
  }
];
```

### Navigation Usage

```typescript
// Current way
router.navigate(['/products', id]);

// Proposed way
router.navigateByName('products.detail', { params: { id: 123 } });
```

### Router Link Usage
```typescript
// Current way
<a [routerLink]="['/products', id]">Product</a>

// Proposed way
<a [routerLinkByName]="'products.detail'" [params]="{ id: 123 }">Product</a>
```

### Route Guards Integration
```typescript
{
  path: 'products',
  name: 'products.list',
  component: ProductListComponent,
  canActivate: [(route) => {
    // route.name would be available here
    console.log(route.name); // 'products.list'
    return true;
  }]
}
```

### Route Resolution
```typescript
// Resolve route by name
const route = router.resolveRouteName('products.detail', { 
  params: { id: '123' } 
});
console.log(route.url); // '/products/123'
```

### Route State Management
```typescript
// Get current route name
const currentRouteName = router.getCurrentRouteName();

// Check if current route matches name
const isProductRoute = router.matchRouteName('products.*');
```

